caption: Amazing views. Great food and services lots of wine options. Very open atmosphere. The heaters are very effective. And the outdoor space is very cozy. This place has it all in terms of ambiance, the terrace is lovely.
(Translated by Google) Very good  (Original) Muy bien
I’ve only been to their shop, but loved the baguette 🥖 and Nutella scone! Great stop while at the wharf.

Would go back to this place just for the tiramisu. Soo so good!!! Its been a while since I have had dessert that delicious. Best part of the meal for sure. The pasta was just okay. Could have been a little more seasoned. The ambiance is beautiful.

The manager is absolutely disrespectful. My friends and I arranged a seating that was promised through the phone. Once we arrived to the restaurant we were told that it was no longer possible. We asked why,  the manager failed to give a factual reason and instead replied “because that’s the way it is” and continued to try to bicker with us (his customers!). Will not come back to this restaurant unless a new manager is hired, where customer service is a priority.
Nice service. Small dishes. Good desserts
Perfect.
My experience was perfect, the service as incredible as the foods&coffee.
Crabs Crabs Crabs 🦀 😋

Unimpressed. Kinda pricey. I went with a friend and we ordered pasta and a side each. We didn’t order any drinks. I got the “Ravioli: Chapel Hill Braised Veal Ravioli. Rosemary. Hen of the Woods. Parmigiano.” ($24) and the “Funghi Trifolati: Sauteed Mushrooms. Olive Oil. Parsley.” ($15). The ravioli pasta (the pasta itself, I think, not the ravioli filling) was oddly crunchy/hard and it arrived room temp/cool. The taste was fine, but it didn’t blow my mind. The mushrooms, though, were amazing - large portion (which it should have been for $15), well seasoned, warmer than my pasta. I probably won’t return on my own volition.
Their terrazza is so cute. I went for the restaurant week and the food was okay. I heard from friends and family that usually their food is great..so might check back!
I had to go twice for work meetings and each time there was a hair in my food so no...I cannot recommend.
Wonderful Atmosphere, Beautiful views and to Die for Food!

Visited recently with friends from out of town during restaurant week and everyone had a great time and meal.  Service was swift, even by covid standards, and our waiter was on point.  Great cocktails as well! Very progressive place and some staff had tasteful social messages on face mask or attire. Given the state of things it's good to see a business allow freedom of expression by their staff.
Excellent Views Great Atmosphere Good Food Good drinks
Food very average considering the high price. Service is inattentive. They overcharged my card by double the amount of the bill I was presented, which I'm now having to try to deal with.

I went to Officina this past Sunday as a part of restaurant week.  My experience was fantastic.  I had the crostini, short rib ravioli, and peach-mint sorbet.  The food was good, but the ravioli in particular stood out; the brown butter sauce was incredible and everything in the food worked together and well.  I really enjoyed my last course as well, as I was given a complementary dessert wine with the sorbet and those items paired together so well and were a great way to end the meal.  I also appreciated the staff consistently wearing masks and the other precautions taken; this was my first time eating inside a restaurant (as opposed to on patios/outside) and they made me feel safe with the precautions taken.  Overall, an incredible meal and an incredible dining experience, especially with how few I’ve had since the pandemic started.  Thank you so much!  I will definitely be back!
Everything authentic!, felt like I'm in Rome 🤩👌

Open for dine-in!  Inconsistently excellent - as you would expect at these prices.  We had to wait for the table but the staff at the front desk was very attentive and offered us a cocktail. Upstairs, we waited over 30 minutes between the appetizer and the main, with little if any acknowledgment.  The highlight of the night were the agnolotti, and the vegetables that came with the salmerino and bistecca thag otherwise weren't as flavorful. The mozzarelle in carrozza and polpette were good too. So were the cannoli. The zabaione was very disappointing: average berries, with foam with little flavor.  Odd selection of music, hard hip-hop followed by classic 70s/80s  Very good social distancing practices:all staff wearing masks, tables well spaced, and contactless payment options
Terrible experienced #1 they push you to have 3 main course option 2# rude waiter 3# manager is okay Stay away !

We went to Officina this evening for an anniversary dinner and could not have been more disappointed. The hostess promised us a 20 minute wait and we were not seated until after an hour had passed (and a manager had intervened). We had been sitting at the bar (where water/condensation drips on guests) and the poor manager realized that something was off and got us seated. The hostess was wearing a mask with a political statement on it - Totally inappropriate for a restaurant employee. I'd like to eat my Italian food without having the views of others shoved in my face. When we finally were seated, we were told that we had to order a 3 course meal for restaurant week. Although this was unexpected, we figured it was fine and at that point we were just happy to have gotten a table (albeit one in the back corner right by the kitchen). The first course was acceptable but the entrees were subpar at best - I ordered a simple spaghetti that came drenched in oil. I've never had a restaurant screw up something so simple. Our waiter was barely present and once again, the manager had to take care of us. The one star is for that young manager, who was the only competent person who deserves to be employed there. My boyfriend had gone to Officina several times before for business lunches so that was why we came this evening, but after tonight, neither of us would ever come back or recommend it. What an unpleasant experience all around.
Food is great. However waited over 2 hours when the hostess said 20 minutes. She never texted or apologized.
Great traditional Italian restaurant the olive oil cake is delicious, great place for a birthday!

Outstanding meal. Exceeded all expectations. Perfect for a special occasion. Can’t say enough good things about the setting on the terrace, service, and meal. We let our server help us order and he did a great job with suggesting the right amount of food and wine pairings. Looking forward to another celebration meal there.
Great fresh pasta and the best roof top in DC.

Great food and atmosphere. Pasta, bread, olive oil, desserts and charcuterie all of best quality. Also love the little deli inside the restaurant and the roof top area. Staff is great too, we usually eat at the bar and the bar tenders are amazing!

Was able to get a rooftop table on a Sunday without a reservation. Our waiter was very helpful with recommending drinks and appetizers to us. I am a big fan of their cocktails and plan on coming back! They had comfy lounge chairs with a nice view of the waterfront, which my waiter recommended us making a reservation ahead of time.
Glad to see them back. The covid environment takes away from the experience,  but food was outstanding!

Haven't had a full meal here (only drinks and appetizers), but I can't say enough incredible things about their rooftop! It's absolutely stunningly decorated and has amazing waterfront views. The speciality cocktails and some of the best I've had, and staff has always been amazing. The few food items I've had were also quite delicious. This place can be quite pricey, but you definitely get great quality drinks and it's worth what you pay.
Eh

I had ordered a pizza here with sausage and mozzarella. The people who worked there said it would be spicy, and I like spicy food. I, however, didn’t like this. When I came home, the grease was dripping from my hands. There was no sausage, or mozzarella, and the pizza itself was abysmal. The dough wasn’t even cooked through fully enough, and to add insult, the toppings on the pizza looked as though it were scrapped from the bottom of the grease trap onto a piece of bread. I was in disbelief that a restaurant I have had good experiences with would serve me this. It’s really a shame because their food was really good but now I won’t be returning again.  I was so disappointed at the quality of this food, I expected much higher quality food coming from a restaurant I have once enjoyed. If I could, I would rate this zero stars.

Ordered dinner through Caviar and wow was the food underwhelming. My gnocchi, other than not looking like the image presented online, was so bland I could have made it better myself. The buratta and veal were good, but overall I expected a lot more for $120 from Officina.

My first time dining here which was by suggestion and invitation of friends who were 30 minutes late. I was 20 minutes early which gave me net of 50 minutes to check out bar(s). I had a Negroni at the main floor bar that was well crafted using my recipe (1 shot gin; 3/4 shot Compari and 1/8 shot sweet vermouth). Negroni was perfect but aloof, sullen service from the bartender. Cost of Negroni $16.00 plus $1.60 tax putting cost at $17.60 plus tip makes it more than a $20.00 drink. Keep in mind I asked for rail gin, nothing from the shelf.  Finishing the drink I learned the other 2 levels have bars and dinner reservation was for second floor seating. My second Negroni at second level bar was equally as good and identically costly. Two bartenders were affable and in good spirits though. My friends arrived and and we were seated for dinner. The center cut, bone-in, pork chop I ordered was terrific. Perfectly grilled and flavorful. Ciabatta bread was outstanding and shared calamari appetizer delicious. I enjoyed house selection of Chianti with dinner. Chianti at $16.00 glass like the Negroni, $17.60. Oh yeah, the great center cut, bone in chop was only $25.00 (I do not know plus tax cost. My friends paid dinner bill). So, I had $52.80 of drinks and $25.00 entree. My question is do I have a drinking problem or is Officina pricing out of line?

If you are looking for a perfect date night this is the place to go!  Great atmosphere, even better food!  Home made pasta to die for, and even better wine selection!  While visiting from NY this week we went two times!  and the service was fantastic.  Our servers were very knowledgeable about the wine and food and helped us with our selections.  Bon appetite!
Great service, great food.
Average, expensive food. Great space.
Good food but a little pricy
The decor was beautiful especially the rooftop where outside you can smoke a cigar..  they provide gas fireplace, blankets pillows.  Beautiful view of the Wharf.
Nice atmosphere & ambiance!

so i realize that officina is probably a dinner place, but my friends and i decided to give bottomless brunch a go.  the ambiance and service were top-notch. i felt like i was dining in a more than 5-star experience, far away from DC. the rooftop, despite having extremely expensive drink prices, was gorgeous and i would go there daily if i could.  however, the brunch food was very, very meh -- and even more meh because of the price! it was $29 a person for bottomless (which ended up being a decent deal since we had 5 people and had 5 bottles of champagne) + entree. the entrees for all of us were very flavorless, seemed even like no one added salt! 3 of us had the burgers (meh, i cuold have made better), one of us had the omelet (said it had zero flavor) an the other had eggs in purgatory (was a very small plate with what looked like 1 egg and 1 can of tomatoes).  i willing to give it a second chance for dinner, but i am not rushing back for such flavorless, small-portioned food for brunch.

Sat downstairs in the bar area. Took quite awhile for the bussers to clear the mess left by the previous patrons as we sat there. They had a variety of imported beers from around the world at a reasonable price. Our server was friendly, and he went above and beyond to answer our questions about the beers.
Service was amazing. Food was great! Go upstairs to the rooftop and get a drink from Mynor! His Irish Coffee and Old Fashioned are next level!
Nice ambiance, friendly staff, great location!
Special restaurant and high quality of all.
Great Service, great ambiance, great spot for a date

Would have been five stars (food was awesome) were it not for the waiter. He was great, right up until he ghosted us. Literally ignored us the last thirty minutes we were there. Wanted to order additional food/drinks. Ultimately gave up! Flagged another waiter to have someone/anyone bring us our check. Went elsewhere to continue our evening.
Good food, good service

We went to the bar for a drink before a show at the Anthem and ordered a few things to share. We asked for a burger to be cut in half and the server said something about he'd request that for us. They bring out this four foot long thing with the absolute worst "pizza" I've set eyes on in my life and shocker it tasted like it looked, elementary school pizza was better... Oh and that burger can you please cut it in half?  The server replied, there is a knife with your silverware. The cocktails were awful too think Bahamas booze cruise mixology without the fun...
No complaints. Good drinks. Sat in the bar area. Had a few appetizers. Not extremely memorable. But I remember enjoying it.

Lowest price bottle of wine $50 but a great selection of wines. Large open space that is well lit. The selection of cheese and chartuceri served with good bread is a nice starter. Lunch selection of excellent quality seafood and pastas, small plates but the quality is prime. A good lunch experience.
Very good service! The sommelier was very friendly and helpful! Our server was adorable!

The food was okay but it was not worth the drama caused by the waitress and manager who ran our credit cards incorrectly. The check was split 4 ways but two of us were charged $10 extra. When we brought it to the attention of the waitress she brought the manager over. He acknowledged they had already realized their mistake before bringing the check to our table and ran the cards again. He said the waitress just brought out the wrong slip. I‘ve never been to a restaurant that isn’t forthcoming with running someone’s card incorrectly. The lack of acknowledgement about running the card wrong originally and the confirmation from the manager that he already knew the card was run incorrectly but didn’t say anything seemed very shady. A week later I had to call back because the wrong charge went through on my card and the same manager told me it’s because I left a $10 tip... on a $37 meal. I’m generous but would never leave 30% on a check that was already messed up. Something very unprofessional and downright wrong is going on there. Beware giving them your credit card information.
Lovely place with over average taste

My friends and I went to dinner here last week. After we paid, one of my friends double-checked her receipt and realized she had been overcharged by $10. We alerted the waitress to the mistake, and she sent the manager over because she said that he was the one who had run my friend's card. The manager was incredibly rude, offered no apology, and acted annoyed that we had noticed the mistake. He ran my friend's card again with the correct amount, and she signed a second receipt. Obviously, the tip she left on this second receipt was lower because the corrected total was lower. My friend checked her bank account a few days later and saw that the tip she had left for the overcharged total had gone through, but the tip she left for the corrected total had not. She called the restaurant and got it fixed, but ultimately, this place left a bad taste in our mouths (pun intended). We definitely won't be coming back here.

I can only comment on the first floor cafe but it was really excellent both times I was there. The sandwiches are so good--excellent bread! Also loved the gelato and cocktails. Warm and inviting atmosphere, as well as good service.

Went here for Restaurant Week. Service was good, ambiance was good, but food left something to be desired. Pasta was very overcooked, steak tartar was chopped very poorly, desserts were interesting but imbalanced.
Went here for happy hour. Cool space with good service but the HH menu was extremely limited. There were probably no more than 5 items on the entire menu, and there were no food options.

I eat in this lovely spot many times a year! This is the best place to dine.  I go there regularly. The meals are very tasty, the staff members are polite and the prices are good. I enjoy being in this spot over a good meal.

I went in looking to partake in the Amaro library. Unfortunately it was having a private tour at the moment. But the two bartenders Carlton and Brady took very good care of me. I was given a lesson in the different types of Amaro and was able to taste a lot of Amaro forward cocktails and had a flight!. The tiramisu is to die for and so is the bread that they give you for an aperitif. Will definitely go back. The only reason why I did not give it a full five stars. because I feel like if they have a tomorrow library it should be big enough to accommodate a private group and other people who want to partake as well.

Fantastic. Attended during restaurant week and had a stupendous time. The food was phenomenal, the staff attentive yet unobtrusive. I also recommend checking out the rooftop bar as it is a great place to hang out in a not relaxed setting.

Absolutely delicious - plan on returning! Had the burrata as an app, the branzino for the entree, and a lime tart for dessert. All were stellar, and the burrata is the best I've ever had. Must try!

Always a positive experience. Great cocktails and exceptional service. If you’re looking for a nice sit down meal while at the wharf, you can’t beat the price and quality of Officina.

Food was great, but the server's demeanor was a little off putting. We had 4 young kids and 4 adults. Asking the server if we can put a couple of their small tables together seemed to annoy the server. My brother has diet restrictions and asked the server if the kitchen would mind heating up his food and bringing it out with everyone else's. Ther server obliged, but with a sense of annoyance.

The place looks very nice and cozy inside, you can get a good view if you sit by the window so you could see the water. The waiter was helpful and polite. The hostess did help to review the menu. When we asked where could we seat she mentioned that they'd like to make money and the upstairs restaurant section was more expensive. So we made the right decision and stayed at the cafe. The ratio of food quantity to the price was little off. The salad was rather small. The pasta dish my son god was very small. The burger and fries were of normal sizes. The flavors. I tasted each meal my family ordered. All of us agreed that everything was over salted. Salad, pasta, burger meat, and french fries had a lot of salt in it.  Also, the salad was sprinkled with something sour but did not feel like a real lemon.  Overall, it was an OK experience but I don't think we would go there again.
Mediocre service. Utensils were missing on our table. Food was ok.
Had the calamari and chicken pram.  Both were fantastic.

Went to Officina for New Years Eve dinner at 5pm. We arrived a bit early so had a seat at the bar area, the bartender seemed to not handle the stress of taking on an additional table of 4. We waited 30 minutes to get our drinks and didn’t even get any water until after the drinks arrived. By this time it was 5:15 and we had to go back to the host stand to see if our table was ready. It was so I’m not sure why we had to go follow up about our own table. By now we got to the main dinning room and the service was too slow. I’m not sure if they had just opened or the floor team was just new, but they didn’t seem confident at all. With it being New Years I was hoping for some high energy and involved service. Our server Walter was very nice. He made some great suggestions and walked us through the menu after getting his footing with the table. The food was EXCEPTIONAL. We ordered an additional calamari, it was that good. The kitchen was the only smooth running operation that evening, and for having an exposed kitchen, my hat’s off to the chef and the kitchen team. Between courses we where reset with fresh silverware but had to asked to have the table wiped first. She set silverware on a messy table. We had several rounds of drinks and I spilled my espresso during desert and after cleaning up no one came over to take our dirty napkins, offer to bring a fresh espresso or even bring new napkins after I ordered a new espresso myself. Overall the service was spotty but the kitchen made up for it with the plates. I’ll be back to try more dishes.
Upscale. .....resturant
Chic Italian eatery and deli. Downstairs cafe is less formal than trattoria upstairs. Helpful staff! Great location for a walk.
Authentic Italian food.
The Truffle event was fabulous! Chef Nick's creations are always sublime! Kudos once again!

Horrible experience. The waiter was good but the servers were very rude as well as the hostess and even the manager was unhelpful. Had to send food back 3 times because it was wrong. We didn’t complain, just paid the bill and we’re leaving when we had a issue getting parking validation. At that time we asked for a manager who was virtually useless. All in all we had a very expensive meal that was sub par.
overrated

Food was mediocre, not up to the standard we had hoped for in what is a nice place, hence the 3 stars. Sides were served lukewarm. Service was fine.

Rather underwhelming dining experience. Selling a 2oz portion of warm water “lobster” on 4 oz of house made pasta, then saying it is too small for entree so order another dish . Failing to inform the customer that it costs $55 and that it would the most expensive seafood dish on offer that night. All for up selling, all for using top fresh ingredients, but if an item is verbalized as a special, let the customer know the cost. Also, if you want to serve Rare lobster, make sure it is at least room temperature and not cold. My seared tuna was seared perfectly- on one side but left raw and unseared on the other. If that is your cooking style, serve the tuna seared side up, the visual would have been significantly improved. I thought the menu sounded great but unfortunately I possibly had a poorly executed meal. It was very busy so you must be doing the vast majority of what you do very well.
Excellent date spot with tasty food and excellent bar staff. Service is very show though (which since they're an Italian joint, is pretty on-brand...), so don't come here in a rush!
Cold, unseasoned and extremely overpriced. About $50 per person for alot of disappointment....

Very authentic Italian. We had a couple of pasta dishes, the duck Ragu which was almost excellent and unique except it was a bit too salty, and the clam linguini. You can taste the handmade pasta as the noodles were cooked to perfection. The beef tartare was good but couldn't match the wagyu version we had previous evening.
Fantastic, as always.
Great resturant...  Love the decoration and the food
Great food and great service.

I've eaten many lunches here and their weekday lunch sandwiches are decent. (Note: if you like their weekday sandwiches, don't expect to get them on the weekend...I was abruptly told by our first server that those are weekday only items. Not sure who made that judgment call.) Decided, however, to have lunch there this past Sunday and boy was it a mistake. For the majority of our meal, our server literally ignored us. When he did stop by to take our order, he was rude and abrupt. While the restaurant replaced our server after benching him, and the manager came over to apologize and offer dessert, they never followed through on their offer. With two little kids ready for a nap, we decided not to bother waiting any further. What I really don't understand is a restaurant that has kids menus bringing kids drinks in glassware. Whoever thought that through...well, really didn't. In the end, though they tried to fix their missteps, and the new server was attentive and far better to the original, the managers overseeing the cafe space need some work.  Following up after owner's response - what does it mean when a restaurant says "send us an e-mail if there's something we can do for you"?
Delicious!    Their crab salad was wonderful but their butternut squash soup was amazing!
This place is amazing. Great food and service.
$24 for 11 tortellini....  Admittedly, they were delicious however it was crazy expensive. We ended the night at Shake Shack.

Had a latte and focaccia, bartender was personable and helpful. Clean and simple spot, loved the connected market with their fantastic food displays
It takes a while to get the bartenders attention here, but the drinks are good.

Love From a sea food state, their calimare was bright and delicious.  Everyone didn't want to share.  My pasta were little presents that once cut did not flatten out.  Cooked to perfection.  Spaghetti was thick and lovely.  We were so happy.
Very good paninis. Authentic Italian soda. It's in an Italian market setting. Very nice on a different plain.

So dissatisfied with the food!  At those prices, one should expect something authentic and delicious. Buca di beppo is a much better option at this point!! *** On a side note, I replied to the manager on September 9th.  Still have not heard back.

I gave this place two star because the server and manager were so great. However, the food was not very good. My husband had the chicken parmesan, which was ok, but a little salty and lacking flavor. We also had tortellini in beef broth (very salty with very little other flavor) and the replacement for the tortellini, gnocchi with lobster mushrooms in a chicken gravy like sauce, which was even saltier. The server and manager were truly great about everything.  I didn't send back the gnocchi because they made such a fuss about the tortellini, I felt bad complaining about how salty the second dish tasted.
Delicious sandwiches on fresh made bread.

It was definitely yummy with some great italian recipes. It's beautiful inside and parking at the wharf is a pain as usual. Service was great.  I was a bit thrown off by how loud it was in there. It's one of the loudest restaurants I've been to in a while.

Officina is a massive Italian restaurant/market/bar near the Maine Avenue Fish Market at the DC Wharf. Overall, we had a great experience except for the service. Here's our experience:  Space: It's a huge, beautifully designed restaurant. The first floor has some seating, a bar, and a market selling fresh pasta, bread, and other Italian goods. The second floor has another bar and a large dining room. There's also outdoor seating on the balcony overlooking the Maine Avenue Fish Market, the oldest continuously operating fish market in the country.  Food: It's definitely quality Italian food. Warm, fresh bread comes to every table and you have the option of still or sparkling water. To start, we ordered the beet salad and burrata, both good (the beet salad has apples in it FYI). I ordered the scallops for my main and it was really delicious. Four large scallops in cream sauce come on a plate.  The only complaint is the service. Our server was not very friendly and very slow. If we needed anything, we had to flag him down several times before he brought it. He never brought us water when we needed it and he forgot to give us the check.  Other than that, it was a good experience.
Food was fresh, very tasty! Host was friendly.
Great pasta: Bolognese and respect your elders whiskey drink. Also amazing service.  (Dining room)

Awesome experience - delicious food, excellent service, beautiful decor. Had the tagliatelle bolognese for dinner, the meatball appetizer (polpetti), and the Nocciola cake for dessert. Every dish was phenomenal. Additionally, their in-house sommelier gave a wonderful recommendation for a bottle of wine. All in all, would definitely recommend and will be back!
Nice view with a chilled beer

Very nice ambience but very limited vegetarian and no vegan options. Not suitable for me.

Small portions and I mean small, no bread, very mediocre food taste and over priced.

** Edit to the review: After submitting my review, the manager contacted me via email and applogised for the service I received. She ensure if I were to give them another chance she will ensure I get the service as it should be and also offered to cover my main course and desert. I went there again last month and had a good time. I like the drinks and appetizers here. It is kind of an expensive place but in the Wharf neighborhood it kind of the average. The entree's are expensive with respect to the flavors expecially the truffle risotto but I was ok with it since it was covered for me. I loved their take on deserts, I tried Baba au Rhum and it was delicious. I ended up paying for lots less than what I would had to but it was worth the experience for the location. The restaurant is very welcoming so woud return to it just for the hospitality and drinks.  Wouldn't recommend this place to anyone. Didn't like the service 1 bit. Had to wait 10 min for drinks on a night where only 3 tables were occupied. The server is also making drinks and is totally unaware of the menu and what they could offer. They are oblivious of their own kitchen closing time. I was waiting for 30 min for someone to take the dinner order, finally had to go and call someone to take our order for food and the guy says it's the last call for food since kitchen is about to close. Takes the order and 10 minutes later manager comes back and says "The kitchen is closed, we cant serve you anything. But please do comeback and we promise to take better care." WTH! Why would I thinking of coming back after such a pathetic service and quality of drinks. Just because these guys are on Wharf, the price isn't justified nethier by the quality of drinks or the service they offer. DC has lot of other better Italian places to try.
highly Overpriced drinks! Average custom service.
Over priced small portions of decent food.  The gnocchi had some decent depth in terms of flavor but honestly it was pedestrian and downright thievery for the price.
Great service. Delicious food and drinks. A little pricey but it was worth it.
Outanding menu and service.....Will be back!!!
Not the highest or best rooftop in the DC Wharf area but has comfortable couches and chairs. Food is solid downstairs also but very young staff seems to be rookies.

Excellent Italian food near the Waterfront in DC. The view from the balcony on the second floor is good. Also, I would recommend trying the dessert wine Ben Rye. It is awesome.

Never leave bad reviews, but this place... Ugh. Ate in the cafe... Nobody there at noon on a Tuesday. I have never left a restaurant so ANGRY and DISAPPOINTED.  For a restaurant that costs so much, I would have expected better service, better people, overall more humanity.  My daughter got an allergic reaction or food poisoning from the food.  We told the staff about how she didn't feel well after her food.  She was rolled up in a ball on the seat.  Nobody came by to ask if she was ok - which I can live with.  But then when we asked the manager about ingredients, he expressed no concern over our 5 year old daughter, pale and dizzy in her seat.  Never offered to replace her food, never tried to get to the bottom of what may have caused, maybe allergy, maybe bad food.  Nobody offered any assistance, so we got our check, paid and left. As I carried my daughter in her ill, limp body, we saw that manager again. Didn't say a word to ask how she was, whether there was anything we needed - water or a bag to be sick in.  I'm not sure this is service, but I am sure that I will never come back to eat here.  One of the reasons why we pay to eat out is to feel like a valued customer.  Instead we felt like an ATM that just paid money for food.  If you want to pay $100 to feel like nobody, go to Officina.

I wish that I could give less than one star. This is quite possibly the worst dining experience I've had in DC. My friend and I both ordered burgers at the bar and after waiting noticed that an order was brought to the bar but not passed out. After 15 minutes of looking at said order, we inquired about whether or not it was one of ours. The bartender told us that he didn't know which of ours it was (we ordered the same thing on different tabs). After figuring out it was not my order, I asked another bartender about an ETA. She kindly noted that my burger was taking 20 minutes longer because it was medium well and not medium. After asking for a manager I was then told by said manager that my food was one minute away from coming out. She did offer a refund to offset the wait...thanks, but where's my food? 20 minutes after the one minute she promised, after being dodged by her and watching her serve other patrons meals, the bartender brings my order. How unclassy and professional. The food nor the drinks are worth the wait or the hassel of back-handed, mediocre service. No thanks ever again.

After an incredible experience at Masseria almost 2 years ago, we've been wanting to try Nicholas Stefanelli's Officina for quite some time and finally found ourselves an occasion this weekend. The Trattoria is well appointed with an open kitchen, airy feel, lots of wood, marble tables, and a nice strip of outdoor seating. We were very shocked that at noon on a beautiful Saturday, the indoor section of the restaurant only had 3 tables including ourselves - it was almost eery how empty it was. After eating, we could see why. We ordered a choice of 7 salumis and formaggios to start. Other than the Nduja, the rest of the salumis were pretty underwhelming - the mortadella was the blandest we've ever had, the prosciutto di parma was excessively chewy. We also ordered several antipasti to share - fried anchovies, bombetta pugliese, and trippa parmagiano. The first two were pretty good. The trippa was not good - it was pretty bland and lacked an "oomph". We tried 3 pastas and a pesce for our mains: bucatini, spaghetti nero, maltagliati, and the gamberoni/prawns. The pastas all lacked flavor - there was nothing that cut through and really wowed us in the flavor. The prawns were extremely disappointing - they were more like oversized shrimp and a bit overcooked. The squid ink pasta's texture was also weird - it felt more like soba noodles. In addition to all this, our server (Ivan?) tried to upsell everything. He advised us 3x to try the Moliterno al Tartufo cheese, which is a +$3 charge. His "favorite" pasta also happened to be the most expensive on the menu. He also tried to sell us burrata to dip with our complimentary bread...even though we already ordered a cheese board. It was suffocating. Yet, through all this, he never once bothered to come over and refill our water glasses. He refilled our water canteen, but never our cups. Overall it was a very disappointing overpriced experience after the delicious food we had at Masseria. We certainly didn't expect Michelin-level, but we expected more - no wonder the restaurant is empty.
